main event: A UFO was observed by a crew approximately 75 miles WNW of JM 2334 (Ohio) on 25 May 1955. The observation lasted 7 minutes, and the UFO was described as stationary.
interesting points: The observation was categorized as Air-Visual and was reported by a crew.
The report indicates that the description of the UFO closely matches that of a balloon.
No follow-up investigation was apparently made, despite the close match to a balloon description.
The UFO was observed for a relatively long duration of 7 minutes, allowing for detailed scrutiny.
The location of the observation was approximately 75 miles WNW of JM 2334 in Ohio.
location: Approximately 75 miles WNW of JM 2334, Ohio
photographs: no, the report does not mention any photographs
